---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Sweden Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/sweden/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Denmark for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/denmark' },
  { title: 'Norway for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/norway' },
  { title: 'Finland for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/finland' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'swedenFit', header: 'Sweden Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'SEK 4,200-5,800/mo', swedenFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'SEK 4,900-6,800/mo', swedenFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'SEK 3,800-5,300/mo', swedenFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'SEK 3,500-5,000/mo', swedenFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Swedish Public (Regions)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: 'Tax-funded', swedenFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'SEK 3,800-5,800', annual: 'SEK 45,600-69,600' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'SEK 5,200-7,500', annual: 'SEK 62,400-90,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'SEK 7,000-10,000', annual: 'SEK 84,000-120,000' },
  { category: 'Swedish Public Healthcare', monthly: 'Tax-funded', annual: 'Max SEK 1,300 patient fees' },
  { category: 'Swedish Private Insurance', monthly: 'SEK 500-1,500', annual: 'SEK 6,000-18,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Sweden 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Sweden. Public healthcare, Stockholm hospitals, residence requirements, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Sweden"
  subheadline="Sweden offers excellent public healthcare, high quality of life, and stunning nature—though immigration requires meeting residency requirements."
  heroImage="/images/countries/sweden-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Sweden</h2>
  <p>
    Sweden offers exceptional quality of life, safety, and public services. The healthcare system is well-funded and comprehensive. While winters are long and dark, summers are magical with midnight sun. Swedes are reserved but friendly, and English is widely spoken.
  </p>

  <p>
    Stockholm combines urban life with archipelago access. Gothenburg offers a more relaxed west coast vibe. Malmö is close to Copenhagen and southern Europe. Smaller cities like Uppsala or Lund provide university-town atmosphere with excellent healthcare.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent public system; tax-funded</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Swedish; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> SEK 25,000-40,000/month (~€2,300-3,700)</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Cold winters with limited daylight; mild summers</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> EU member (not Eurozone; uses SEK)</li>
      <li><strong>Nature:</strong> Allemansrätten (right to roam) allows nature access</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Sweden's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Sweden's healthcare is decentralized to 21 regions, each running its own system. Care is tax-funded with nominal patient fees (max SEK 1,300/year out-of-pocket cap). Quality is excellent, with well-equipped hospitals and trained staff.
  </p>

  <p>
    Wait times for specialist care can be long—the guarantee is max 90 days to specialist, 90 days to treatment, but it's not always met. Emergency care is immediate. Many Swedes add private insurance for faster specialist access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Wait Times Reality</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      While Swedish healthcare is excellent, wait times for non-urgent specialist care and elective procedures can be months. The "care guarantee" (max 90 days) isn't always achieved. Private insurance for faster access is increasingly common among those who can afford it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Sweden's immigration for non-EU retirees is limited:
  </p>

  <h3>Self-Employment Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Starting a business in Sweden provides residence rights. Must prove viable business plan and sufficient funds. Not strictly retirement but can work for active retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Family Reunification</h3>
  <p>
    If you have Swedish citizen or resident family, reunification is possible. Your family member must demonstrate ability to support you and provide accommodation.
  </p>

  <h3>EU Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register with Skatteverket (tax authority) after arrival. Demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage. After registration, access Swedish healthcare.
  </p>

  <h3>No Retirement Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Unlike some countries, Sweden doesn't have a specific retirement visa. Non-EU retirees typically need family connection, business activity, or other qualifying circumstances.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Sweden:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; register with region for permanent access</li>
    <li><strong>After registration:</strong> Swedish public healthcare access via personnummer</li>
    <li><strong>Private option:</strong> Many add for faster specialist access</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Sweden</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for initial residence application. Once you have a personnummer (Swedish ID), you access the public system. Many maintain private Swedish insurance for faster specialist care. International coverage remains useful for travel and home country visits.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Sweden, these providers offer appropriate coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Sweden</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Scandinavian network, good for initial period</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive European pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Swedish Private:</strong> Skandia, If offer faster specialist access</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Sweden.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Sweden reflect the high local price level:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Get personnummer:</strong> Swedish public healthcare is nearly free once registered</li>
    <li><strong>Private Swedish:</strong> Cheaper than international once resident</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> SEK 50,000+ deductible if using public system</li>
    <li><strong>Sweden exclusion:</strong> Once in public system, exclude Sweden from international</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American with Swedish Spouse, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Married to Swedish citizen. Moving to Stockholm via family reunification.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for residence application. After personnummer, access public system. Keep Cigna for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~SEK 5,000/month. After: public free + Cigna ~SEK 3,000/month (Sweden excluded).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British EU Citizen, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Retained EU citizenship via another country. Moving to Gothenburg.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EHIC initially. Register for personnummer. Add Swedish private insurance (Skandia) for faster care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Public access after registration + Skandia ~SEK 1,200/month. BUPA for UK visits.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Finnish Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Nordic citizen moving from Helsinki to Malmö. Finnish pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Nordic agreement allows easy transfer. Register, get personnummer, access Swedish system.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Swedish public (free with cap). Optional private top-up ~SEK 1,000/month.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can non-EU retirees move to Sweden?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        It's difficult. Sweden doesn't have a retirement visa. You typically need: family in Sweden (reunification), business activity (self-employment), or other qualifying circumstances. Pure financial independence isn't a pathway like in some countries.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How dark is winter really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very dark in northern Sweden (above Arctic Circle sees no sun for weeks). Stockholm gets about 6 hours of daylight in December. Many people experience seasonal affective disorder. Light therapy is common. However, summer has the opposite—long twilight evenings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is English really enough?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For daily life in cities, yes. Swedes have excellent English. However, administrative processes are in Swedish, and integrating socially is easier with Swedish. Healthcare can be delivered in English in major centers, but learning basic Swedish improves the experience.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why do Swedes use private insurance if public is good?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Wait times. While public healthcare quality is excellent, waiting months for specialist consultations or elective procedures is common. Private insurance (SEK 500-1,500/month) provides faster access through private clinics. Many employers offer it as a benefit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Sweden.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Swedish Migration Agency and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
